NAME		passwd
SYNTAX		passwd
DESCRIPTION	Change your password.
		Unless your local administrator has overidden the default
		behaviour, passwords are checked for security on the following
		points:

            1. Password must be at least six characters in length.
            2. Password must contain at least one a-z character
               and at least one non a-z character.
            3. Password must not contain any character repeated
               more than thrice.
            4. Password must not be a pseudo-anagram of your
               username.
            5. Password must not contain consecutive sequences of
               more than three characters.
            6. Password must not contain more than four
               characters from your old password.

